<p>Instead of treating a web page as a single massive document, these frameworks allow developers to build encapsulated, reusable UI components (like a button, a nav bar, or a complex data table) that manage their own state. React, developed by Facebook, popularized the Virtual DOM, a technique that optimizes rendering performance by only updating the parts of the actual DOM that have changed.</p>

